  "text": "The areas in the shadowed interior of the gallery forests produce less algae and biomass of floating plants than the sunny areas, but they receive more dead leaves, branches and dead trunks, which play a crucial role in the energetic balance of the system [CITATION_1] . Substrates of dead trees are generally sources of diversity and abundance for invertebrates.",
